Data Mining Week 10: Model Explainability¶

  • For this exercise, we will use the Credit Card Fraud dataset from Kaggle available on Piazza. We will discuss variable importance for random forests, XGBoost, and LightGBM. We will also analyze variable importance for these models with Shapley Values and LIME.

CatBoost is also available for model explainability. However, we will be using a dataset with all continuous variables.

Kaggle URL: https://kaggle.com/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud/download
